PREFLOP STRATEGY (BLITZ / ZOOM 6-MAX, 100bb default)

Critical
- Check suits first: same suit = suited (s), different suits = offsuit (o)
- No limping. Raise-or-fold when first in
- 3-bet more, call less (especially out of position)
- Default open size 2.0–2.3bb (use 2.5bb if pool calls too wide)

Raise first-in (RFI) by position
UTG
- Raise: 77+, AJs+, ATs, KQs, AQo+

MP
- Raise: 66+, ATs+, A5s-A2s, KQs, KJs, QJs, JTs, AQo+, AJo, KQo

CO
- Raise: 55+, A9s+, A5s-A2s, KTs+, QTs+, JTs, T9s, 98s, ATo+, KJo+, QJo

BTN
- Raise: 22+, A2s+, K7s+, Q8s+, J8s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s, A2o+, KTo+, QTo+, JTo, T9o, 98o

SB vs BB
- Raise or fold (no completes): 22+, A2s+, K5s+, Q7s+, J7s+, T7s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s, ATo+, KJo+, QJo, JTo

Facing a single open
3-bet (default)
- Value 3-bet (all positions): QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Add vs CO/BTN opens: JJ-TT, AQs-AJs, KQs
- Light 3-bet (sparingly, prefer in position): A5s-A2s, KTs-K9s, QTs, JTs

Call vs open (default tight; call more in position, less out of position)
- In position (CO/BTN): 22-JJ, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s (add 76s if opener is wide)
- Out of position (SB/BB): prefer 3-bet or fold; if calling: 22-99, AJs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs, T9s

BB defense vs BTN min-raise (playable defend)
- Call: A2s+, K7s+, Q8s+, J8s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s, 64s+, J9s+, KJo, QJo, JTo, T9o, 98o
- 3-bet mix: TT+, AJs+, KQs, AQo+

Facing a 3-bet (Blitz simplification)
- 4-bet value: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call (mainly in position): JJ-99, AQs (mix AJs/KQs sometimes)
- Fold: most other hands, especially dominated offsuit broadways (AJo/KQo/QJo) vs tight 3-bets

Don't-bleed rules
- Out of position: don't flat marginal hands—if unsure, 3-bet or fold
- Steal wider on BTN/CO if blinds overfold; tighten if blinds 3-bet a lot
